Building image in local:
1. sudo docker build -t ai-tool-backend:3.2 . 

Push image to Docker:
1. sudo docker login
2. sudo docker build -t harnath/ai-tool-backend:3.2 .  
3. sudo docker push harnath/ai-tool-backend:3.2

Pull image from Docker:
1. sudo docker pull harnath/ai-tool-backend:3.2

Run image:
1. sudo docker run -d --restart=always --name ai_tool_ds harnath/ai-tool-backend:3.2   # --restart=always to restart image when it goes down
1. sudo docker run -d --restart=always --name ai_tool_ds --log-driver=json-file --log-opt max-size=100m --log-opt max-file=5 harnath/ai-tool-ds:3.1
2. sudo docker run --name ai_tool_ds harnath/ai-tool-ds:3.1

Kill the image:
1. docker ps
2. docker stop [container_id]  # stoping 
3. docker rm abcdef123456 # to delete that container

Image created from this repo: 
1. ai-tool-ds  (DS main logic)
2. cron-update-interview-status (scheduler which updates status for records with in-progress, ds-error)



Alembic:
alembic init migrations   # to create migrations
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "Initial migration"
alembic upgrade head   # to upgrade migrations
alembic upgrade <target_version>  # from version head to target_version
alembic stamp <target_version> # this will set head manually to requeste target_version